<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-30T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="605" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">881.01/10–2144: Airgram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-30T16:00:00-04:00">October 30, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>A–585. The Department would like to receive from the Embassy such
                                information as may be available concerning the present Spanish
                                attitude toward Spain’s future position in Tangier. In this
                                connection <pb facs="0568" n="556" xml:id="pg_556"/> reference is
                                made to telegrams no. 312 of October 19 and 313 of October 21 from
                                the Legation at Tangier. Since the latter telegram appears not to
                                have been repeated to Madrid the Embassy will doubtless wish to ask
                                Tangier for the text. Is it the opinion of the Embassy that the
                                withdrawal of Spanish regiments has any association with this
                                question, as suggested by the Legation?</p>
                            <p>Copy to Tangier.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>